column2: Come now, dear friend, Papa Nurgle will make things right...
Do you wish to stop questing?
Do you wish to stop raiding?
Do you wish to stop studying magic?
I'll go. I have no choice.
It's good to be the Phoenix King.
Ursun, I met my brother in spirit.
I return home - For the Lady!
I shall quest for the Grail!
I shall seek out the Gods!
I wonder who will die first?
Men, get me out of here!
Not now, but later, for sure!
No, I prefer life to undeath.
No, that one is not worthy.
I will donate to our cult's coffers.
What would it take to enact a grand rite?
Prepare to initiate a grand rite!
On a dark and stormy night...
I will donate to our cult's coffers.
What would it take to enact a grand rite?
Prepare to initiate a grand rite!
We must send for a witch hunter immediately.
No, Witch hunters cause too much trouble.
Indeed, time to return to the temple.
I... ehh, heresy? No no, let me explain!
A good cultist is a good liar! This is proof of guilt!
All heretics must die by fire!
I'm sure you are not a heretic.
I... ehh, heresy? No no, let me explain!
A good cultist is a good liar! This is proof of guilt!
All heretics must die by fire!
I'm sure you are not a heretic.
Do not bother me with such news again.
I must inform my liege at once!
Yes, of course - get to work at once.
No, not like this - I was promised eternal life!
Yes, I shall ask my liege!
Yes, I will face my Gods!
After ruling their lands for so long, this ruler has earned some trust from their vassals.

This ruler has reigned for generations, proving to their vassals their capability.

Only those beings blessed with  centuries of lifespan ever remember this character's ascension to power. They've ruled for so long, it's hard to imagine their lands without them.
Only those beings blessed with  centuries of lifespan ever remember this character's ascension to power. They've ruled for so long, it's hard to imagine their lands without them.
This ruler has outlived centuries, enduring and lording over their vassals without ever faltering. They've always ruled, they likely always will.
Tradition states the Phoenix Crown to be wore by a man, whereas the Queen takes the spiritual leadership of Avelorn as Everqueen. Going against such a tradition is not well thought of.
Tradition states Avelorn to be held by the Everqueen. Going against such a tradition is not well thought of.

Since time immemorial, Ulthuan has been governed by the conjoined rule of a Phoenix King and an Everqueen, to be arrogant enough to claim absolute dominion over the Asur is cause for great outrage amongst High Elves.
This King has not yet tested himself passing through the flames of Asuryan. Until he submits himself to this trial, his claim to rulership remains dubious amongst the other Princes.
This Asur has not yet made clear is stance over the possible involvement of Ulthuan in external affairs.
